cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving the training of neural machine translation systems, which is a natural language processing (NLP) task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses optimization techniques for neural networks, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to training neural networks, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions experiments with different language pairs, which could suggest a category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) if the experiments involve image-based translation.
